---
title: SpacesSync — runtime sync workflow (ROADMAP — same shape as current; documents design intent)
---
flowchart TD
    classDef user fill:#1e3a5f,stroke:#4a90e2,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef macos fill:#3a3a3a,stroke:#888,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#eee
    classDef spoon fill:#1f4d2e,stroke:#4caf50,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef decision fill:#5a4a1e,stroke:#d4a853,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef terminal fill:#4a1f1f,stroke:#e57373,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff
    classDef ui fill:#3d2a4d,stroke:#b07cc6,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#fff

    %% ============================================================
    %% READING NOTE
    %% ============================================================
    %% Each node opens with a <b>bold lead</b> for quick-skim.
    %% Detail follows for the deeper reader.
    %% This roadmap is intentionally near-identical to CURRENT —
    %% the design goal is met by today's code; this diagram
    %% documents what we deliberately do NOT do.
    %% ============================================================

    %% ============================================================
    %% KEY CONCEPTS — read this first
    %% ============================================================
    KEY["<div style='text-align: left;'><b>Key concepts — read this first</b><br/><br/>• <b>Space</b> — a macOS virtual desktop on a single display. Each display has its own list.<br/>• <b>Sync group</b> — a list of displays that should track each other. When any one switches Space, the others follow.<br/>• <b>Trigger display</b> — the display the user actually switched. <b>Target display</b> — another display in the same sync group that we drive to match.<br/>• <b>Watcher</b> = hs.spaces.watcher. Fires our callback on any Space change. Does NOT tell us which display — we have to diff.<br/>• <b>gotoSpace</b> = hs.spaces.gotoSpace. Programmatically switches a display to a given Space. macOS drops rapid back-to-back calls — hence switchDelay.<br/>• <b>lastActiveSpaces</b> — snapshot of prior per-display Space state. We diff against this to find what changed.<br/>• <b>is_running</b> <i>(roadmap rename of syncInProgress)</i> — simple boolean. true while dispatching gotoSpace calls and through the post-chain debounce. Single global flag, not per-group.</div>"]:::keybox
    classDef keybox fill:#0d1a26,stroke:#4ab3c6,color:#cfe6f0,text-align:left

    %% ============================================================
    %% MAIN FLOW
    %% ============================================================

    U(["<b>User switches a Space.</b><br/>Via Mission Control gesture, ⌃→/⌃←,<br/>a Dock click, or other macOS UI."]):::user
    OS["<b>macOS commits the switch.</b><br/>The chosen Space is now active on that display."]:::macos
    W["<b>Watcher fires our callback.</b><br/>hs.spaces.watcher invokes our Lua callback —<br/>the only signal we get from macOS that something changed."]:::macos

    GATE_ENABLED{"<b>Is SpacesSync enabled?</b><br/>(false after the user toggles off via the<br/>toggle hotkey or :stop)"}:::decision
    SKIP_DISABLED[/"<b>Return — SpacesSync is off.</b><br/>How we got here: user pressed the toggle hotkey<br/>(default ⌃⌥⌘Y), or called spoon.SpacesSync:stop()<br/>from init.lua, the Hammerspoon console, or hs -c.<br/><br/>Why we still need this guard: when :stop runs,<br/>macOS may already be partway through calling our<br/>watcher function. You can't kill an in-flight call —<br/>so this guard makes that one straggler bail out<br/>instead of finishing a sync the user just stopped."/]:::terminal

    GATE_RUNNING{"<b>Already running a sync chain?</b><br/>is_running == true while we are dispatching<br/>gotoSpace calls AND through the post-chain<br/>debounce window."}:::decision
    DROP[/"<b>Drop the event.</b><br/>This is the whole point of is_running:<br/>swallow our own gotoSpace echoes and the<br/>phantom fires that follow Space animations.<br/>Side effect: real user swipes inside this<br/>~1.4s window are also dropped (see design panel)."/]:::terminal

    DIFF["<b>Diff to find what changed.</b><br/>Compare hs.spaces.activeSpaces against lastActiveSpaces<br/>to find which display(s) just switched."]:::spoon
    FIND{"<b>Did anything actually change?</b><br/>Did at least one display's active Space change<br/>since the last snapshot?"}:::decision
    NO_CHANGE["<b>No actual Space change — exit.</b><br/>The watcher fires on more than real Space switches:<br/>Mission Control opening, display reconfiguration,<br/>animation settling, Stage Manager events.<br/>The diff confirms nothing actually changed —<br/>refresh the snapshot defensively and exit."]:::spoon

    LOOKUP["<b>Find the trigger's sync group.</b><br/>Map the trigger display's UUID → position number,<br/>then scan syncGroups for a group containing that position."]:::spoon
    GROUP{"<b>Trigger in a sync group?</b><br/>Is the trigger display a member of any group?"}:::decision

    INDEPENDENT["<b>Independent display — nothing to sync.</b><br/>Trigger is not in any sync group.<br/>We never set is_running on this path,<br/>so there's no chain to wait out and<br/>no flag to clear afterward."]:::spoon

    LOCK["<b>Set is_running = true.</b><br/>From now until the post-chain debounce expires,<br/>watcher fires are dropped."]:::spoon

    SYNCNEXT[/"<b>Iterate target displays.</b><br/>Targets = sync-group members minus the trigger.<br/>Start at i = 1."/]:::spoon
    TARGET["<b>Sync this target to the trigger's index.</b><br/>1. Compute the Space ID at the trigger's index<br/>   on this target display.<br/>2. Dispatch hs.spaces.gotoSpace targetSpaceID.<br/>3. macOS animates the Space switch on the target."]:::spoon
    DELAY["<b>Wait switchDelay (0.3 s).</b><br/>macOS silently drops back-to-back gotoSpace calls;<br/>the gap lets each one settle before the next is dispatched."]:::macos
    MORE{"<b>More targets?</b><br/>Any target displays remaining in the sync group?"}:::decision

    POPUP["<b>Show popup on trigger display.</b><br/>The active Space index with names from the<br/>workspace name store. Auto-dismisses after popupDuration."]:::ui

    DEBOUNCE["<b>Start debounce timer (0.8 s).</b><br/>is_running stays true through this window so<br/>phantom fires from animation settling are still<br/>dropped (they fire after the last gotoSpace dispatch)."]:::spoon

    REENABLE["<b>Clear is_running — re-arm watcher.</b><br/>Set is_running = false<br/>(this is the half of the toggle we owe<br/>after raising it for the sync-group path);<br/>refresh lastActiveSpaces from current state;<br/>watcher is ready for the next user switch."]:::spoon

    UPDATE_BASELINE["<b>Update lastActiveSpaces baseline.</b><br/>Set lastActiveSpaces = currentSpaces<br/>so the next watcher fire diffs against<br/>the post-switch state."]:::spoon
    DONE(["<b>Watcher armed.</b><br/>Ready for the next user Space switch."]):::terminal

    %% ============================================================
    %% EDGES
    %% ============================================================

    U --> OS --> W --> GATE_ENABLED
    GATE_ENABLED -- no --> SKIP_DISABLED
    GATE_ENABLED -- yes --> GATE_RUNNING

    GATE_RUNNING -- "yes — chain is running" --> DROP
    GATE_RUNNING -- "no — idle" --> DIFF --> FIND
    FIND -- no --> NO_CHANGE --> DONE
    FIND -- yes --> LOOKUP --> GROUP

    GROUP -- no --> INDEPENDENT --> POPUP
    GROUP -- yes --> LOCK --> SYNCNEXT --> TARGET --> DELAY --> MORE
    MORE -- yes --> SYNCNEXT
    MORE -- no --> POPUP

    POPUP -- "independent path:<br/>(is_running was never set —<br/>no debounce or re-arm needed)" --> UPDATE_BASELINE --> DONE
    POPUP -- "sync-group path:<br/>(is_running is true —<br/>must debounce, then clear it)" --> DEBOUNCE --> REENABLE --> DONE

    %% ============================================================
    %% DESIGN INTENT — what we deliberately do and don't do
    %% ============================================================

    DESIGN["<div style='text-align: left;'><b>Design intent — what we accept and what we don't try to fix</b><br/><br/><b>The goal:</b> only human-initiated swipes trigger the sync system. Our own gotoSpace calls must NOT cause secondary syncs.<br/><br/><b>How we achieve it:</b> a single global is_running boolean. Set true at chain start, cleared after debounce. Every watcher fire during that window is dropped, no questions asked.<br/><br/><b>What gets dropped (intentionally):</b><br/>• ✅ Echoes of our own gotoSpace dispatches — the whole point<br/>• ✅ Phantom fires from macOS Space animations settling — happens during debounce, also dropped<br/><br/><b>What gets dropped (accepted side effect):</b><br/>• ⚠ Real user swipes inside the ~1.4s ignore window. We accept this. Users don't typically swipe multiple times in under a second; if it happens, the user just swipes again. Not worth solving.<br/><br/><b>What we deliberately don't build:</b><br/>• ⊘ Pending trigger / drain step / bounded retry loop — overengineering for a use case that doesn't exist.<br/>• ⊘ Echo classifier (compare changed Space against expectedActiveSpaces) — solves the same non-problem.<br/>• ⊘ Eager baseline update (write lastActiveSpaces[target] before each gotoSpace) — would let us drop is_running entirely, but adds correctness risk if gotoSpace is silently dropped by macOS. Not worth the invasiveness.<br/><br/><b>Difference from CURRENT:</b> functionally none. Possible cosmetic improvement: rename syncInProgress to is_running for readability. That's it.</div>"]:::designbox
    classDef designbox fill:#1f1d0d,stroke:#d4a853,color:#f0e8c8,text-align:left
